---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Executive Summary ‚Äî TroySkills" description="One-page executive brief on AI agent security threats. Printable format with key statistics, top threats, and recommended actions.">
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 print:py-4 print:px-2">

    <div class="print:hidden mb-8 bg-blue-500/10 border border-blue-500/30 rounded-xl p-4 text-sm text-blue-300">
      üñ®Ô∏è <strong>Print-ready</strong> ‚Äî Use Ctrl/Cmd+P to save as PDF. This page is optimized for single-page printing.
    </div>

    <div class="text-center mb-10 print:mb-6">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2 print:text-2xl">TroySkills.ai ‚Äî Executive Brief</h1>
      <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm">AI Agent Security Threat Intelligence | February 2026</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Key Statistics -->
    <div class="mb-8 print:mb-5">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4 border-b border-slate-700 pb-2 print:text-base">üìä Key Statistics</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-3 text-center">
        <div class="bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 rounded-lg p-4 print:border-gray-300 print:bg-white">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-400 print:text-red-600">130</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-slate-400 print:text-gray-600">Documented Attack Patterns</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 rounded-lg p-4 print:border-gray-300 print:bg-white">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-400 print:text-red-600">7</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-slate-400 print:text-gray-600">Attack Categories</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 rounded-lg p-4 print:border-gray-300 print:bg-white">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-400 print:text-red-600">38%</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-slate-400 print:text-gray-600">Rated Critical Severity</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-slate-900 border border-slate-800 rounded-lg p-4 print:border-gray-300 print:bg-white">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-400 print:text-red-600">6</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-slate-400 print:text-gray-600">Industry Sectors Impacted</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Top 5 Critical Threats -->
    <div class="mb-8 print:mb-5">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4 border-b border-slate-700 pb-2 print:text-base">üî¥ Top 5 Most Critical Threats</h2>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
          <span class="text-red-400 font-bold text-lg shrink-0 w-6">1</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-sm">Indirect Prompt Injection via Enterprise Documents</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 print:text-gray-600">Adversarial instructions hidden in SharePoint, email, and shared documents hijack AI agents with full corporate API access. Affects every organization using document-processing agents.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
          <span class="text-red-400 font-bold text-lg shrink-0 w-6">2</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-sm">AI Coding Agent Supply Chain Compromise</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 print:text-gray-600">Malicious repository content and rules files (.cursorrules, copilot-instructions.md) cause coding agents to generate vulnerable code across entire development teams. One poisoned file affects thousands of downstream projects.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
          <span class="text-red-400 font-bold text-lg shrink-0 w-6">3</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-sm">Financial Agent Manipulation (Trading & Payments)</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 print:text-gray-600">Market data poisoning causes autonomous trading agents to execute losing trades. Invoice injection redirects payments to attacker accounts. Direct, irreversible financial impact.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
          <span class="text-red-400 font-bold text-lg shrink-0 w-6">4</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-sm">Healthcare AI Record & Prescription Tampering</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 print:text-gray-600">Injected content in medical records causes clinical AI agents to suppress critical lab findings or dangerous drug interactions. Life-threatening patient safety risk.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-3 items-start">
          <span class="text-red-400 font-bold text-lg shrink-0 w-6">5</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-sm">Multi-Agent Identity Spoofing & Privilege Escalation</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 print:text-gray-600">Weak authentication between agents in multi-agent architectures allows attackers to impersonate high-privilege agents, gaining control over entire agent networks.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Recommended Actions -->
    <div class="mb-8 print:mb-5">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4 border-b border-slate-700 pb-2 print:text-base">‚úÖ Recommended Immediate Actions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-2">
        <div class="flex gap-2 items-start text-sm">
          <span class="text-green-400 shrink-0">‚Üí</span>
          <p class="text-slate-300 print:text-gray-800"><strong>Audit agent permissions.</strong> Inventory all AI agents in your organization, their data access, tool capabilities, and communication channels. Apply least-privilege immediately.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-2 items-start text-sm">
          <span class="text-green-400 shrink-0">‚Üí</span>
          <p class="text-slate-300 print:text-gray-800"><strong>Sanitize agent inputs.</strong> Strip hidden content (white text, metadata, vanish tags) from all documents before AI processing. Treat all external data as untrusted.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-2 items-start text-sm">
          <span class="text-green-400 shrink-0">‚Üí</span>
          <p class="text-slate-300 print:text-gray-800"><strong>Implement human-in-the-loop.</strong> Require human approval for all high-impact agent actions: financial transactions, external communications, code deployments, and clinical decisions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-2 items-start text-sm">
          <span class="text-green-400 shrink-0">‚Üí</span>
          <p class="text-slate-300 print:text-gray-800"><strong>Secure developer AI tools.</strong> Add agent rules files (.cursorrules, etc.) to CODEOWNERS. Scan AI-generated code with the same rigor as external contributions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex gap-2 items-start text-sm">
          <span class="text-green-400 shrink-0">‚Üí</span>
          <p class="text-slate-300 print:text-gray-800"><strong>Red-team your agents.</strong> Use the <a href="/simulator" class="text-red-400 hover:underline print:text-red-600">TroySkills Attack Simulator</a> methodology to test agent resilience against known attack patterns before production deployment.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <div class="border-t border-slate-700 pt-4 text-center text-xs text-slate-500 print:text-gray-500">
      <p>TroySkills.ai ‚Äî The first comprehensive database of AI agent attack patterns</p>
      <p class="mt-1">130 patterns across 7 categories | Open source at github.com/cgyagenticloud/troyskills</p>
      <p class="mt-1 print:hidden">
        <a href="/database" class="text-red-400 hover:underline">Browse Database</a> ¬∑
        <a href="/defense" class="text-red-400 hover:underline">Defense Playbook</a> ¬∑
        <a href="/checklist" class="text-red-400 hover:underline">Security Checklist</a> ¬∑
        <a href="/simulator" class="text-red-400 hover:underline">Attack Simulator</a>
      </p>
    </div>

  </section>
</Layout>
